            "id": "s_l5_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Data, Data 📡",
            "content": "Most apps need to fetch data from a server (like weather, news, tweets).\n\nWe use the global function `fetch()`."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l5_2",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Fetching JSON 📦",
            "content": "`fetch()` returns a **Promise**!\nIt's perfect for `async/await`.",
            "codeSnippet": "async function getWeather() {\n  let response = await fetch('https://api.weather.com');\n  let data = await response.json();\n  console.log(data);\n}",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": false
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l5_3",
